00:11:58,625 --> 00:12:01,375
[TEACHER] As I'm sure you recall
from your early biology courses,

208
00:12:01,458 --> 00:12:03,541
modern day mammals,
birds, reptiles,

209
00:12:03,625 --> 00:12:06,083
and amphibians have six legs.

210
00:12:06,166 --> 00:12:08,375
It is widely believed
that this originated with fish,

211
00:12:08,458 --> 00:12:11,666
whose pectoral, front ventral,
and rear ventral fins

212
00:12:11,750 --> 00:12:15,791
grew over many generations until
they eventually became limbs.

213
00:12:17,041 --> 00:12:18,333
[TEACHER] The genes
that determined the shape

214
00:12:18,416 --> 00:12:21,333
of the pectoral fins
duplicated to form ventral fins,

215
00:12:21,416 --> 00:12:25,500
which duplicated again
to form rear ventral fins.

216
00:12:25,583 --> 00:12:27,500
Of course, in prehistoric times,

217
00:12:27,583 --> 00:12:29,625
there were also
four-legged amphibians,

218
00:12:29,708 --> 00:12:33,125
but they died out and
left no surviving descendants.

219
00:12:33,208 --> 00:12:35,500
Most likely, extra limbs
evolved because six legs

220
00:12:35,583 --> 00:12:37,208
were more advantageous than four

221
00:12:37,291 --> 00:12:39,458
when it came to
supporting body weight.

222
00:12:39,541 --> 00:12:43,041
Humans are the ultimate
product of evolution.

223
00:12:43,125 --> 00:12:46,583
We can be broadly divided
into four different groups.

224
00:12:48,333 --> 00:12:49,583
[TEACHER]
The first of these groups

225
00:12:49,666 --> 00:12:53,541
includes the catfolk, the
goatfolk, and the fauns.

226
00:12:53,625 --> 00:12:57,875
In the next group are the
angelfolk and the draconids.

227
00:12:57,958 --> 00:13:00,500
The third group is the centaurs.

228
00:13:00,583 --> 00:13:03,500
Weretigers were also included
in this group at one time,

229
00:13:03,583 --> 00:13:06,958
but unfortunately
they are now extinct.

230
00:13:07,041 --> 00:13:10,083
Finally, we have the merfolk,
though none of the students

231
00:13:10,166 --> 00:13:14,083
in this room are
part of that group.

232
00:13:14,166 --> 00:13:16,666
In the past, the differences
between the four groups

233
00:13:16,750 --> 00:13:19,375
led to discrimination
and distrust,

234
00:13:19,458 --> 00:13:21,416
often culminating in war.

235
00:13:21,500 --> 00:13:24,166
Of course, had the four-legged
amphibians survived,

236
00:13:24,250 --> 00:13:27,333
become the dominant race,
and evolved into humans,

237
00:13:27,416 --> 00:13:29,375
things would be very different.

238
00:13:31,750 --> 00:13:33,250
[TEACHER] There would
likely still be differences

239
00:13:33,333 --> 00:13:36,583
in hair, skin, and eye color,
but nothing significant enough

240
00:13:36,666 --> 00:13:39,541
to lead to serious
discrimination.

241
00:13:39,625 --> 00:13:42,208
However, the idea of
a world in which humans

242
00:13:42,291 --> 00:13:44,750
have just four limbs is absurd.

243
00:13:44,833 --> 00:13:47,083
Something out of
a fantasy novel.

244
00:13:47,166 --> 00:13:50,250
In reality, we must
remain vigilant at all times

245
00:13:50,333 --> 00:13:54,041
if we wish to avoid the fear
and chaos of global conflict.

246
00:13:54,125 --> 00:13:56,541
Some nations are still
plagued with violence,

247
00:13:56,625 --> 00:13:58,666
while others strive for
the harmony that comes

248
00:13:58,750 --> 00:14:01,000
from accepting each
group's differences.

249
00:14:01,083 --> 00:14:02,958
We can only achieve
unity by viewing others

250
00:14:03,041 --> 00:14:06,666
as neither greater
nor lesser than ourselves.

251
00:14:06,750 --> 00:14:09,916
Therefore, equality is the key,

252
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:13,333
the virtue we must strive
for above all others.

253
