Huh? Huh...

258
00:14:49,958 --> 00:14:51,125
[NOZOMI]
Go faster.

259
00:14:51,208 --> 00:14:52,250
Hey, go faster.

260
00:14:52,333 --> 00:14:53,625
C'mon, go faster.

261
00:14:53,708 --> 00:14:55,500
Can't you go any faster?

262
00:14:55,583 --> 00:14:57,291
If you're about to collapse
after two kilometers

263
00:14:57,375 --> 00:15:00,291
you should really
start exercising more.

264
00:15:00,375 --> 00:15:03,375
I'm not a natural athlete, okay?

265
00:15:03,458 --> 00:15:04,958
[pants]

266
00:15:05,041 --> 00:15:08,541
You know, I don't get why we all
have to run the same distance.

267
00:15:08,625 --> 00:15:10,416
Doesn't seem fair.

268
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:11,916
Mom and I run every day.

269
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:13,833
We do about twenty kilometers.

270
00:15:13,916 --> 00:15:15,416
It's not so bad.

271
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:17,041
Why do you run so much?

272
00:15:17,125 --> 00:15:18,500
A weight-loss thing?

273
00:15:18,583 --> 00:15:21,125
Well, uh...

274
00:15:21,208 --> 00:15:22,625
[NOZOMI]
You don't look that big to me.

275
00:15:22,708 --> 00:15:24,125
Uh?!

276
00:15:24,208 --> 00:15:25,041
[chuckles]

277
00:15:25,125 --> 00:15:26,250
When centaurs gain weight,

278
00:15:26,333 --> 00:15:28,125
we have a hard time
turning our bodies,

279
00:15:28,208 --> 00:15:30,583
so we can't do stuff like
wiping our own behinds.

280
00:15:30,666 --> 00:15:31,875
Oh, wow.

281
00:15:31,958 --> 00:15:33,875
I didn't think you
could reach that far.

282
00:15:33,958 --> 00:15:34,958
[HIMENO gasps]

283
00:15:35,041 --> 00:15:36,375
Of course, I can!

284
00:15:36,458 --> 00:15:38,000
'Kay, sorry.

285
00:15:39,708 --> 00:15:44,416
I need... a break...

286
00:15:47,666 --> 00:15:48,750
[NOZOMI]
If you don't get in shape,

287
00:15:48,833 --> 00:15:50,833
you won't be able to
wipe your own butt.

288
00:15:50,916 --> 00:15:52,375
I hate you!

289
00:15:52,458 --> 00:15:55,208
No matter how much you eat,
you never gain weight, do you?

290
00:15:55,291 --> 00:15:57,125
[KYOKO]
No, not really.

291
00:15:57,208 --> 00:15:58,208
You're lucky.

292
00:15:58,291 --> 00:15:59,708
[chuckles]

293
00:15:59,791 --> 00:16:00,916
Hey. Hold on.

294
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:03,125
What was that chuckle for?

295
00:16:03,208 --> 00:16:05,416
Well, your body's
nothing but straight lines.

296
00:16:05,500 --> 00:16:08,291
Doesn't seem like something
to be jealous of to me.

297
00:16:09,333 --> 00:16:11,416
I'll punch you, you jerk!

298
00:16:11,500 --> 00:16:12,916
[NOZOMI laughs]

299
00:16:13,916 --> 00:16:14,916
[KYOKO]
You!

300
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:15,666
[NOZOMI]
You'll have to catch me first.

301
00:16:15,750 --> 00:16:16,416
[KYOKO]
Okay! I will!

302
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:17,916
[NOZOMI]
Good luck!

303
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:20,083
Hey, you're actually
running pretty fast.

304
00:16:20,166 --> 00:16:28,000
[KYOKO pants]
I can't... Have to stop...

305
00:16:30,666 --> 00:16:31,750
[HIMENO]
Are you okay?

306
00:16:31,833 --> 00:16:33,750
Jeez, you look like
you're about to die.

307
00:16:33,833 --> 00:16:36,208
[KYOKO]
And whose fault is that?

308
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:43,208
[HIMENO] Do you want me
to carry you on my back?

309
00:16:43,291 --> 00:16:44,791
[KYOKO]
No way.

310
00:16:44,875 --> 00:16:46,291
That's a terrible idea.

311
00:16:46,375 --> 00:16:47,708
I'd be accused of discrimination

312
00:16:47,791 --> 00:16:51,083
and sent to a
correctional clinic.

313
00:16:51,166 --> 00:16:52,833
[NOZOMI]
That's a little dramatic.

314
00:16:52,916 --> 00:16:55,750
It really isn't, actually.

315
00:16:55,833 --> 00:16:58,583
In our country, centaurs
used to be warriors,

316
00:16:58,666 --> 00:17:01,541
but in some places, they
were slaves used as mounts.

317
00:17:01,625 --> 00:17:04,458
That's where most anti-
discrimination laws originated.

318
00:17:04,541 --> 00:17:07,250
They take this stuff seriously.

319
00:17:07,333 --> 00:17:10,875
Jeez, even talking like
this is probably illegal.

320
00:17:10,958 --> 00:17:12,666
[NOZOMI] Anyway, once
you've caught your breath,

321
00:17:12,750 --> 00:17:14,375
we'll take our time finishing.

322
00:17:14,458 --> 00:17:15,833
No. I'm fine.

323
00:17:15,916 --> 00:17:17,250
Go on ahead without me.

324
00:17:19,958 --> 00:17:21,041
Don't worry,
it's not like we're trying

325
00:17:21,125 --> 00:17:22,958
to get first place or anything.

326
00:17:23,041 --> 00:17:25,625
I bet you that's what
Tama's going for, though.

327
00:17:25,708 --> 00:17:28,166
Yeah, because being
class president isn't enough.

328
00:17:30,541 --> 00:17:32,500
[NOZOMI] For the record, though,
if there was a cash prize,

329
00:17:32,583 --> 00:17:34,500
I would ditch you
in a heartbeat.

330
00:17:34,583 --> 00:17:36,458
[moans]

331
00:17:36,541 --> 00:17:38,708
'Kay, let's go.

332
00:17:38,791 --> 00:17:40,208
Huh? Already?

333
00:17:40,291 --> 00:17:43,208
[NOZOMI] We still need to make
it back to school on time.

334
00:17:43,583 --> 00:17:45,750
[NOZOMI]
Come on! Let's get moving.

335
00:17:48,583 --> 00:17:50,250
[NOZOMI]
We'll take it easy, okay?

336
00:17:57,875 --> 00:17:59,375
Huh?

337
00:18:01,500 --> 00:18:03,291
Hey, Hime?

338
00:18:03,375 --> 00:18:04,708
[HIMENO]
Hmm?

339
00:18:04,791 --> 00:18:05,791
If you try,

340
00:18:05,875 --> 00:18:09,083
I bet you can go
really fast, huh?

341
00:18:09,166 --> 00:18:10,791
[HIMENO]
Mm...

342
00:18:10,875 --> 00:18:13,791
I can do a hundred meters
in nine seconds or so.

343
00:18:13,875 --> 00:18:14,916
Is that fast?

344
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:17,166
[NOZOMI]
Yeah, crazy fast.

345
00:18:17,250 --> 00:18:18,958
[HIMENO]
I can show you if you want.

346
00:18:19,041 --> 00:18:20,291
There are no cars coming.

347
00:18:20,375 --> 00:18:22,000
I'll just run to the stoplight.

348
00:18:22,083 --> 00:18:23,791
[NOZOMI]
Okay, be careful, though.

349
00:18:23,875 --> 00:18:27,083
[KYOKO]
Ready. Set. Go!

350
00:18:28,541 --> 00:18:29,125
Oh, wow!

351
00:18:29,208 --> 00:18:30,000
Too fast.

352
00:18:30,083 --> 00:18:31,458
She's not gonna stop in time!

353
00:18:31,541 --> 00:18:34,500
Hey! Stop, Hime!

354
00:18:51,833 --> 00:18:54,000
[OLD MAN]
Hey, kid! Be careful!

355
00:18:54,083 --> 00:18:55,958
I'm sorry!

356
00:18:59,416 --> 00:19:01,333
[NOZOMI]
Hime!

357
00:19:01,416 --> 00:19:03,000
Hey, are you okay?

358
00:19:03,083 --> 00:19:03,791
Uh-huh.

359
00:19:03,875 --> 00:19:05,250
[laughs]

360
00:19:05,333 --> 00:19:07,250
It isn't funny.

361
00:19:07,333 --> 00:19:09,458
You are crazy fast, huh?

362
00:19:09,541 --> 00:19:10,750
You should run track.

363
00:19:10,833 --> 00:19:13,916
I doubt there's anybody
who could beat you.

364
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:18,083
[HIMENO] Umm...
Yeah, that's not exactly true.

365
00:19:18,166 --> 00:19:19,958
I actually gave it a try once.

366
00:19:20,041 --> 00:19:21,500
[STARTER]
Ready!

367
00:19:22,333 --> 00:19:24,541
[HIMENO]
Hey, wait!

368
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:27,583
Oh, right.

369
00:19:27,666 --> 00:19:29,041
I forgot the heats
were divided by race.

370
00:19:29,125 --> 00:19:30,291
Yep.

371
00:19:30,375 --> 00:19:33,666
Okay, but what about a
sport like basketball?

372
00:19:33,750 --> 00:19:35,291
[NOZOMI]
Uh...

373
00:19:35,375 --> 00:19:36,750
[NOZOMI]
Here! Pass!

374
00:19:40,041 --> 00:19:44,625
Hime has the horsepower,
but she's not very graceful.

375
00:19:45,958 --> 00:19:47,333
[KYOKO]
Too bad what a waste.

376
00:19:47,416 --> 00:19:49,000
But still, it's gotta
be pretty nice

377
00:19:49,083 --> 00:19:51,166
being faster
than most people.

378
00:19:51,250 --> 00:19:54,125
You could be faster if you
worked out once in a while.

379
00:19:54,208 --> 00:19:56,625
Hey, you've been leaning
on me long enough.

380
00:19:56,708 --> 00:19:58,166
Huh?

381
00:19:59,833 --> 00:20:01,750
Hey, wait for me.

382
00:20:05,375 --> 00:20:06,875
Pick up the pace, you three.

383
00:20:06,958 --> 00:20:08,541
We haven't got all day, here.

384
00:20:08,625 --> 00:20:10,541
The lunch break is almost over.

385
00:20:10,625 --> 00:20:11,791
Yes, ma'am.

386
00:20:11,875 --> 00:20:13,750
[NOZOMI]
Wait, is that?

387
00:20:16,625 --> 00:20:18,166
[KYOKO]
What are you doing on there?

388
00:20:18,250 --> 00:20:20,333
Oh, hi.

389
00:20:20,416 --> 00:20:24,708
Well, I didn't get much sleep
last night, so I'm worn out.

390
00:20:24,791 --> 00:20:26,208
I hope you can make it, Kyoko.

391
00:20:26,291 --> 00:20:27,833
We don't have any
more room on the bike.

392
00:20:27,916 --> 00:20:30,041
Huh? Aww...

393
00:20:30,125 --> 00:20:32,291
[COACH] All right, that's
enough chit-chat, ladies.

394
00:20:32,375 --> 00:20:34,333
[AKECHI]
See ya!

395
00:20:34,416 --> 00:20:36,291
[INUKAI]
Good luck.

396
00:20:36,375 --> 00:20:40,125
[KYOKO moans]

397
00:20:40,208 --> 00:20:41,541
Whining isn't gonna help.

398
00:20:41,625 --> 00:20:42,291
Now, let's go.

399
00:20:42,375 --> 00:20:43,875
[HIMENO]
Huh?

400
00:20:43,958 --> 00:20:45,000
Hold on.

401
00:20:45,083 --> 00:20:46,041
Hey, Nozomi!

402
00:20:46,125 --> 00:20:48,166
You're going the wrong way!

403
00:20:48,250 --> 00:20:50,291
The patrol's already
passed us, right?

404
00:20:50,375 --> 00:20:52,250
So, let's take a shortcut.

405
00:20:52,916 --> 00:20:55,666
[KYOKO] I guess you have
good ideas once in a while.

406
00:20:55,750 --> 00:20:57,291
[NOZOMI]
Shut up, slow poke.

407
00:20:58,041 --> 00:20:59,833
[HIMENO]
Is this really okay?

408
00:21:00,708 --> 00:21:02,541
[KYOKO pants]

409
00:21:02,625 --> 00:21:04,375
Shortcut or not.

410
00:21:04,458 --> 00:21:05,458
I'm beat!

411
00:21:05,541 --> 00:21:06,875
[NOZOMI]
Serves you right.

412
00:21:06,958 --> 00:21:09,125
Maybe that'll teach you
not to slack off all the time.

413
00:21:09,208 --> 00:21:11,041
[HIMENO] You can do it.
We're almost there.

414
00:21:11,125 --> 00:21:13,458
[KYOKO moans]

415
00:21:13,541 --> 00:21:15,250
[MANAMI]
Took you long enough. Hurry up!

416
00:21:15,333 --> 00:21:16,958
Afternoon classes are starting.

417
00:21:17,041 --> 00:21:19,583
[KYOKO moans]

418
00:21:36,583 --> 00:21:38,000
Yay!

419
00:21:38,083 --> 00:21:38,791
Whoa.

420
00:21:38,875 --> 00:21:41,291
You look sick. Why?

421
00:21:41,375 --> 00:21:44,333
What's your rank? Huh?

422
00:21:46,416 --> 00:21:47,958
[KYOKO]
Oh...

423
00:21:48,041 --> 00:21:49,833
Well, that sucks.

424
00:21:54,583 --> 00:21:57,250
What did you say
about slacking off?

425
00:21:57,625 --> 00:21:58,541
It's okay.

426
00:21:58,625 --> 00:22:00,416
We can all study together.

427
00:22:00,500 --> 00:22:03,208
You know you spoil
her too much, right?

